{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father said no, because we knew as long as she will be well-fed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But she did it out of humanity and out of very good relationship with my brother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "How she-- how-- she's all right, this Gentile.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She saved his life later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's a different story.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we got the money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was not our worry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when did things start to get really bad, that your lives were at risk?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From 1942.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From 1942, they started to ship the first shipments-- I call it shipments-- the transports to Poland, because Auschwitz-- what is it called in English?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Auschwitz--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see how you have a [? blackout? ?] Auschwitz was in-- under construction.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew it was not ready.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These 1,000 young men and 1,000 young boys-- women, they were the ones who went to Auschwitz to build the physical start of the Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One person, who we know here from this group of 1,000 girls is still alive and lives here.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know her because she comes from Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other girl who was taken, was the sister of my wife.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was one year older.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She didn't return.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Nobody returned, only the one which I know here returned, because she was put, right from the beginning in Auschwitz, in an office.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She spoke four languages fluently-- German fluently, Hungarian, Slovak.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So the Germans needed-- for establishing the administration, they needed such people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she was lucky that she got that job.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Usually, from these 2,000 people, almost nobody survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the transportation started.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From 1942, when we already knew they-- they took-- tomorrow night-- we-- we got our spies in the official administration.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew a day before, sometimes two days before, don't sleep home, because they are coming to collect Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
